  <text>
      <body>
         <div type="entry">
            <pb facs="https://leaf.bucknell.edu/sites/default/files/2026-01/diary31.jpg"/>
            <head><date>Friday 31st</date></head>
            <p><name type="weather">The wind blew pretty hard all day, and this evening set in with storm and rain</name>.
               This morning we saw a little <objectName>schooner</objectName> standing in toward us, running hard before
               the stiff nor-wester, steered like a hog, the sailors said, badly steered. One of
               our <objectName>gunboats</objectName> ran out to her, she dropped <objectName>sail</objectName> and was towed in. It had on board 2
               New Yorkers, 1 New Jersey man &amp; one N. Carolinian - they had been impressed
               into a company. answered roll call last night, stationed at <placeName key="Middleton" ref="http://www.wikidata.org/entity/Q6841976">Middleton</placeName>, <placeName key="Hyde County" ref="https://sws.geonames.org/4472505">Hyde
               County</placeName>, just across the sound, &amp; came in this morning. There were 800
               stationed there - they said it was reported that there were ten thousand at
               <placeName key="Roanoke Island" ref="https://sws.geonames.org/4488228">Roanoke Island</placeName> and that we had 30,000 We received our <objectName>mail</objectName> this afternoon about a
               bushel &amp; a half. I rec'd 3 letters from <persName key="John" ref="http://www.wikidata.org/entity/Q4925477">John</persName> &amp; <persName key="Annie" ref="http://www.wikidata.org/entity/Q566893">Annie</persName> of the 7.14. 20.
               January.</p>
         </div>
